		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">World view</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>A <b>comprehensive world view</b> (or <b>worldview</b>) is a term <a href="/wiki/Calque" title="Calque">calqued</a> from the <a href="/wiki/German_language" title="German language">German</a> word <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Weltanschauung" class="extiw" title="wikt:Weltanschauung">Weltanschauung</a></b></i> (<span class="IPA nounderlines" style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Media:De-Weltanschauung.ogg" title="Media:De-Weltanschauung.ogg"><img alt="De-Weltanschauung.ogg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" border="0" /></a> <a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/De-Weltanschauung.ogg" class="internal" title="De-Weltanschauung.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ˈvɛlt.ʔanˌʃaʊ.ʊŋ]</span></a> <small class="metadata">(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">help</a>·<a href="/wiki/File:De-Weltanschauung.ogg" title="File:De-Weltanschauung.ogg">info</a>)</small></span>) <i><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Welt" class="extiw" title="wikt:Welt">Welt</a></i> is the German word for "world", and <i><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Anschauung" class="extiw" title="wikt:Anschauung">Anschauung</a></i> is the German word for "view" or "outlook." It is a concept fundamental to German <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">philosophy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Epistemology" title="Epistemology">epistemology</a> and refers to a <i>wide world perception</i>. Additionally, it refers to the framework of ideas and beliefs through which an individual interprets the <a href="/wiki/World_(philosophy)" title="World (philosophy)">world</a> and interacts with it. The German word is also in wide use in <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a>, as well as the translated form <i>world outlook</i> or <i>world view</i>.</p>
